<item>
            <title>[LU-4642] unify lu_object_{find,locate} interfaces to return &quot;-ENOENT&quot; for NULL case</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4642</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, lu_object_locate() will return NULL for the case of not found the required object (slice), but related lu_object_find_xxx() may return &quot;-ENOENT&quot; for that. Such inconsistent behaviour will confuse the callers. We prefer to make them all to return &quot;-ENOENT&quot; for the case of not found the object.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
